Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -eux

    # Install Python and pytest
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state expected by the automated tests
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------

    # 1. Create the base directory structure
    mkdir -p /home/user/sample_queries
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user/sample_queries

    # 2. Create the two sample SQL files with EXACT content & single LF
    printf "SELECT * FROM orders WHERE order_date > '2023-01-01';\n" \
        > /home/user/sample_queries/orders.sql
    printf "SELECT * FROM inventory WHERE quantity < 10;\n" \
        > /home/user/sample_queries/inventory.sql

    chmod 644 /home/user/sample_queries/orders.sql
    chmod 644 /home/user/sample_queries/inventory.sql

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Clean up apt caches to keep image small
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%labels
    Maintainer "Apptainer Task Setup"
    Description "Environment for query-tuning playground task with initial sample SQL files."

%help
This container provides the starting environment for the “query-tuning playground”
task.  It includes:

• /home/user/sample_queries/orders.sql  
• /home/user/sample_queries/inventory.sql  

and has pytest pre-installed for the automated validation suite.

All work should be done under /home/user as described in the task instructions.